<subSubSection id="D9F16554FFB1BA1DB718F453B672FC3C" pageId="13" pageNumber="632" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="915436DFFFB1BA1DB718F453B672FC3C" blockId="13.[778,1374,705,1128]" pageId="13" pageNumber="632">
<taxonomicName id="56EB4D5CFFB1BA1DB718F453B19CFC9A" baseAuthorityName="Gundlach" baseAuthorityYear="1861" box="[778,954,819,852]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Eumops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="632" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ferox">Eumops ferox</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="56EB4D5CFFB1BA1DB7DCF453B658FC9A" baseAuthorityName="G. M. Allen" baseAuthorityYear="1932" box="[974,1150,819,852]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Eumops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="632" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="floridanus">E. floridanus</taxonomicName>
, and E. wilson: were formerly classified as subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="56EB4D5CFFB1BA1DB718F4E2B197FC6D" authorityName="Wagner" authorityYear="1843" box="[778,945,898,931]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Fumops" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="13" pageNumber="632" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glaucinus">E. glaucinus</taxonomicName>
but are distinct species here based on morphological and molecular differences. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
